The method introduced by Priestley and Subba Rao to detect weak
nonstationarity[] consist in estimating locally the spectral density
function of the signal and then to test the hypothesis that it doen't
vary statistically over time -if so, it would be weakly stationary.
As the whole procedure is old, is fast and reliable under conditions
found on filtered signals to test statinarity as a yes/no.
Data was filtered to remove trends and periodic components using
STL algorithm[], then PSR test was performed over every epoch at
every channel for all the subjects [approx. 1 hour per subject].
